So far, so good, but I'm just getting into the first test/exploration log. I gotta point out that actual radio protocol that the word  after the first sentence and then say it again at the end of the transmission.

That's the only radio faux pas I see in the first one, other than both of them dropping the  altogether after a few lines.

Now in the Lambda-12 exploration log, there is a new thing. Shotguns really aren't measured by caliber, rather by gauge. So the  might be a low gauge, like 10 or even 8. Or it could be standard 12 gauge loaded with slug rounds. Well, you could find slug rounds for any gauge, but 12 is the easiest to maintain a standard arsenal with, since in a pinch you could scavenge ammo from pretty much anywhere.

Aside from that, this was a pretty good read. I'm glad I already avoid Disney like the plague when I can.







